at 7 month follow-up, while on HAART for WHO (World Health Organisation) stage 
IV disease. The dynamics of HIV-related immunosuppression has an impact on the 
clinical course of SSPE. Contrary to reported cases of fulminant progression, a 
classic presentation with slow progression can be expected in children on HAART. 
We reemphasize the recommendation of "early measles vaccination" to prevent 
measles infection and subsequent SSPE in these children with an increasingly 
good life expectancy in the era of HAART.

