Individualized positron emission tomography-based isotoxic accelerated radiation 
therapy is cost-effective compared with conventional radiation therapy: a 
model-based evaluation.

Bongers ML(1), Coupé VM(2), De Ruysscher D(3), Oberije C(4), Lambin P(4), Uyl-de 
Groot CA(5).

Author information:
(1)Department of Epidemiology and Biostatistics, VU University Medical Center, 
Amsterdam, The Netherlands. Electronic address: ml.bongers@vumc.nl.
(2)Department of Epidemiology and Biostatistics, VU University Medical Center, 
Amsterdam, The Netherlands.
(3)Radiation Oncology University Hospitals Leuven/KU Leuven, Leuven, Belgium; 
Department of Radiation Oncology, GROW Research Institute, Maastricht University 
